The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                A 50-year-old woman was killed and two others were injured when a taxi hit a rickshaw at Sukantanagar, near Chingrihata, on Tuesday. Parbati Das and her husband Bhola, who were on the rickshaw, were flung off when the taxi lost control and hit them, police said. Rickshawpuller Bablu Dey too was injured. The three were taken to Bidhannagar State General Hospital, where Parbati was declared dead. The others were admitted. The taxi driver fled with his vehicle.     Two men were found lying unconscious in a coach of the Bagh Express on Tuesday afternoon at Howrah station. GRP officers said Guddu Singh, 32, and his father Ramaeswar, 54, of Siwan in Bihar, had been drugged and robbed on the train. They were admitted to Howrah District Hospital.    A fire broke out at a fish market near Howrah station on Tuesday night. Fire department officials said thermocol cartons stacked in the market caught fire and the flames soon spread to other parts of the market and an adjacent abandoned building. Five tenders fought the blaze for an hour. No one was injured.     British deputy high commissioner Sanjay Wadvani on Tuesday urged businessmen to invest in low carbon businesses and make most of the business opportunities associated with climate change, which was close to three trillion US dollars. Speaking at a meet at the Indian Chamber of Commerce, Wadvani asked industry not to be afraid of climate change or wait for the government to act. Senior state pollution control board officials present at the meeting said India could not compromise on its development agenda in the name of climate change.     V.N. Tripathi has taken over as general manager of the Eastern Railway. He was the general manager of Metro Railway in Calcutta before his current posting.     A knee clinic has been started at Apollo Gleneagles Hospitals. Similar clinics have been opened in 16 other cities across the country.     President Pratibha Patil will visit Calcutta on December 7 to attend a programme at the Saha Institute of Nuclear Physics. Governor Gopalkrishna Gandhi and chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee will receive her at the airport, said a state home department source.     Siddhartha Dutta, the pro vice-chancellor of Jadavpur University, was referred to as vice-chancellor in the Metro report Varsity plans security rejig published on November 24. The error is regretted.            
